{
  "text": "Painful fissures may appear on the palms, fingertips, soles of the feet and toes, and on the lips [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Fissures should be treated with emollients, and sealed with cyanoacrylate or flurandernolide tape that delivers high-potency steroids and protects against mechanical trauma 61 .",
